Implementation file: src/claim-office.ts

Test: quote a sword, then claim with negative damage amount.

```typescript
const input = {
  customer: { yearsWithMHPCO: 0 },
  steps: [
    { op: "quote", items: [{ type: "sword", material: "steel", enchantment: 0, cursed: false }] },
    { op: "claim", policy: 0, incident: {
      cause: "fire",
      damages: [{ itemType: "sword", amount: -200 }]
    }}
  ]
};
expect(() => claimOffice(input)).toThrow();
```

Current implementation doesn't validate damage amounts, so it will compute negative reimbursement (which gets clamped to 0 by the > 0 check). It won't throw.

EXPERIMENT MODE: Run autonomously, proceed to Green after completion.
You MUST output the full Step 7 block verbatim (both Compilation
Prediction and Runtime Prediction lines, each with Correct or
Incorrect). Do not abbreviate. Do not collapse the two prediction
lines into one.

